>[Question]
>If a man travels 14miles at 36mph  and then 7miles at 18mph on his 
>journey to work what is his average speed and how do you work this 
>out?
>
>[Difficulty]
>have not got a clue how to work this out
>
>[Thoughts]
>have none

Hello Karen,

I think we are to assume the information relates to a single journey.  Also, the term 
"average speed" has a technical meaning for a journey.  It is total distance traveled divided 
by the total time.  One doesn't work out the speed on the two legs of the journey and 
average them.


